All the meals were prepared fresh on site each day and were all local produce and organic. 

Breakfast would consist of eggs, fresh fruit salad, with a small glass of freshly squeezed orange juice.

A typical lunch would be fish or chicken brochettes cooked on the BBQ and a selection of salads, and dinner would be a soup and a chicken tagine, all served by the villa’s waiting staff.

The calorie intake for each day would be limited to around 1,200 Kcal and the output of exercise around 2,000 Kcal, and generally most camper lose around 9lbs over the week.

